1
00:00:00,510 --> 00:00:03,070
You get rid of one,
and another one just pops up.

2
00:00:04,010 --> 00:00:05,110
What a headache.

3
00:00:05,940 --> 00:00:08,110
I have to get rid of them
once and for all.

4
00:00:09,010 --> 00:00:10,010
Manager Lee.

5
00:00:10,420 --> 00:00:13,990
Can you think of a good way
to get rid of Oh Jang Mi?

6
00:00:17,920 --> 00:00:19,760
Just how far is Mom willing to go?

7
00:00:20,460 --> 00:00:22,260
How can she say something so terrifying?

8
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:33,000
How about we trade lives?

9
00:00:34,310 --> 00:00:35,310
Seo Rin.

10
00:00:36,210 --> 00:00:37,410
Let's do it.

11
00:00:38,580 --> 00:00:42,080
I want to know
why you were separated from Mom...

12
00:00:43,050 --> 00:00:44,050
and ended up living there.

13
00:00:45,080 --> 00:00:46,580
I'm going to find out...

14
00:00:48,020 --> 00:00:49,020
who your parents are.

15
00:01:12,910 --> 00:01:13,910
Hello, Jang Mi.

16
00:01:14,310 --> 00:01:16,050
- What's up?
- Seo Rin.

17
00:01:16,380 --> 00:01:17,820
Let's play a fun little game.

18
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:21,050
- What kind of game?
- Like you suggested before,

19
00:01:21,650 --> 00:01:23,760
how about we try switching places?

20
00:01:24,060 --> 00:01:25,660
- What?
- Just for one day.

21
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:27,460
Any longer and we'll get caught.

22
00:01:27,730 --> 00:01:30,130
Let's just switch for one day.
What do you say?

23
00:01:32,600 --> 00:01:34,000
What should I do?

24
00:01:36,730 --> 00:01:39,240
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

25
00:01:39,340 --> 00:01:40,540
Mom, you had a bad cold,

26
00:01:40,540 --> 00:01:42,340
but you got better right away
after taking your medicine, didn't you?

27
00:01:42,740 --> 00:01:46,910
Mom, you need to make sure you bundle up
so you don't get sick again, okay?

28
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:49,410
Jang Mi, you're so pretty.

29
00:01:49,410 --> 00:01:51,650
Jang Mi is Suk Hee's daughter.

30
00:01:56,150 --> 00:01:58,560
Yes, even if it's just for one day.

31
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:01,530
Just for a single day,
I want to see her up close.

32
00:02:01,690 --> 00:02:04,100
Seo Rin! Are you even listening to me?

33
00:02:05,560 --> 00:02:07,730
Deal! It does sound fun.

34
00:02:08,570 --> 00:02:12,640
Is this that twin telepathy thing?

35
00:02:13,870 --> 00:02:15,740
Meet me at the cafe where we met before.

36
00:02:15,810 --> 00:02:19,010
Okay. I'm leaving right now.

37
00:02:19,210 --> 00:02:22,680
Are you worried I'll back out?
See you in an hour.

38
00:02:23,050 --> 00:02:26,150
And you haven't told anyone, right?

39
00:02:26,650 --> 00:02:28,450
- What?
- Shit!

40
00:02:28,450 --> 00:02:31,060
Did you tell anyone about the twin thing?

41
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:34,190
No, I didn't.
I was just about to tell Baek Ho...

42
00:02:34,260 --> 00:02:37,060
What?
You already told Lawyer Kang Baek Ho?

43
00:02:37,130 --> 00:02:41,030
No, I was going to, but I haven't yet.

44
00:02:42,030 --> 00:02:46,100
Wait, how do you know Baek Ho?

45
00:02:47,340 --> 00:02:48,410
How do you think?

46
00:02:48,910 --> 00:02:51,010
Do you think there's anything
I don't know about you?

47
00:02:51,310 --> 00:02:54,280
Come on, what's that supposed to mean?
You're joking, right?

48
00:02:54,350 --> 00:02:58,420
Anyway, don't you dare tell anyone.
Understood?

49
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:00,550
This has to be our secret.

50
00:03:01,090 --> 00:03:03,490
- Got it?
- But why?

51
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:05,760
What do you mean, "why?"
Because my mother...

52
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:08,760
Because we look so much alike.

53
00:03:09,030 --> 00:03:11,430
We don't just look alike. We're identical.

54
00:03:11,860 --> 00:03:14,530
But why do I have to keep it a secret?

55
00:03:14,530 --> 00:03:15,530
Shit.

56
00:03:15,730 --> 00:03:17,600
Why are you so full of questions?

57
00:03:18,140 --> 00:03:21,510
It might not matter to you if we're twins,
but it's a huge deal for me.

58
00:03:21,940 --> 00:03:24,680
I have a lot more at stake than you do.

59
00:03:25,980 --> 00:03:29,650
Anyway, just keep your mouth shut, got it?

60
00:03:30,550 --> 00:03:33,220
I'll only meet you
if you promise to keep it a secret.

61
00:03:33,820 --> 00:03:36,650
And that's the only way
I'll tell you what I know.

62
00:03:37,060 --> 00:03:40,760
This is getting more confusing.
Honestly, I'm full of questions.

63
00:03:40,890 --> 00:03:44,260
Exactly. So for now,
stop trying to figure it all out,

64
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:48,200
- just keep your promise to me!
- Fine. I get it.

65
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:51,340
What a temper. Just don't be late.

66
00:04:00,650 --> 00:04:03,950
Okay. I won't say a word.

67
00:04:05,050 --> 00:04:07,690
Wait. You won't say a word?
What does that mean?

68
00:04:09,020 --> 00:04:11,720
That was...

69
00:04:12,820 --> 00:04:14,390
You were on the phone
with someone for a while.

70
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:16,290
Did you think I was them?

71
00:04:19,060 --> 00:04:21,800
- Yes.
- That stings a little.

72
00:04:22,300 --> 00:04:23,900
So, you're not going to tell me
who that was?

73
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:26,240
Don't tell me it's a secret from me, too?

74
00:04:27,210 --> 00:04:31,340
I'm sorry, but yes.
I'll tell you everything later.

75
00:04:32,310 --> 00:04:33,310
All right.

76
00:04:33,950 --> 00:04:35,850
You must have your reasons
for not telling me right now.

77
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:37,520
I'll wait.

78
00:04:42,090 --> 00:04:44,620
Looks like Baek Ho ran straight
to the side-dish girl...

79
00:04:44,960 --> 00:04:47,260
the moment he got off work.

80
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:50,400
- I wonder what he sees in her.
- Mom, have some of this.

81
00:04:52,430 --> 00:04:53,430
Jun Ho.

82
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:55,970
You know, I was thinking...

83
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:57,670
and something seems off.

84
00:04:58,240 --> 00:05:00,270
- What is?
- What seems off?

85
00:05:00,470 --> 00:05:02,370
That CEO Chae woman.

86
00:05:03,210 --> 00:05:04,710
After giving you such a hard time,

87
00:05:05,080 --> 00:05:07,750
why would she suddenly promote you
to General Manager?

88
00:05:08,210 --> 00:05:11,980
- Don't you think that's suspicious?
- For goodness' sake.

89
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:14,490
You're too suspicious.

90
00:05:14,490 --> 00:05:17,990
She clearly realized how talented
Jun Ho is and promoted him accordingly.

91
00:05:17,990 --> 00:05:19,220
Why would there be an ulterior motive?

92
00:05:19,960 --> 00:05:21,030
Right, Jun Ho?

93
00:05:21,860 --> 00:05:24,360
Actually, like Mom said,
something feels off to me too.

94
00:05:24,700 --> 00:05:29,000
I'm worried she'll give me a big project
just to find fault and make me quit.

95
00:05:29,930 --> 00:05:33,170
Hey, don't think like that.
CEO Chae isn't that kind of person,

96
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:34,440
and a company is meant
to operate professionally.

97
00:05:34,510 --> 00:05:38,240
It's not a place where promotions
are based on personal feelings.

98
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:39,510
I'm not so sure.

99
00:05:40,380 --> 00:05:41,580
Is that really all there is to it?

100
00:05:45,020 --> 00:05:46,750
You should've seen it, Manager Lee.

101
00:05:48,220 --> 00:05:50,390
I'm talking about the part
where Yeom San Wol got a nosebleed.

102
00:05:51,660 --> 00:05:54,230
I'm worried she might threaten
to leave the house over this.

103
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:55,760
That would be even better.

104
00:05:56,960 --> 00:06:01,200
If Yeom San Wol leaves, what can she do?
She has no tricks up her sleeve.

105
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:04,140
Anyway, the Chairman is something else.

106
00:06:04,140 --> 00:06:05,400
Who knew he would blindside her like that?

107
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:08,440
He must have had this planned all along.

108
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:10,680
That's just how that old man is.

109
00:06:11,280 --> 00:06:14,910
He pushes everyone away and trusts no one,
so of course he has no one around him.

110
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:19,150
He only trusts Seo Rin,
his own flesh and blood.

111
00:06:19,750 --> 00:06:23,450
- Gosh, Mom! What are you doing?
- Let go of me.

112
00:06:24,260 --> 00:06:28,730
Seriously! Mom!
Why are you suddenly packing your bags?

113
00:06:29,330 --> 00:06:31,630
I'm so humiliated and furious
that I can't live here anymore.

114
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:34,230
I've never been so humiliated
in my entire life!

115
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:38,640
I got all dressed up in a wedding gown
for a so-called wedding,

116
00:06:38,700 --> 00:06:41,940
only to end up having dinner
with the family at a restaurant.

117
00:06:41,970 --> 00:06:43,340
I must be the first woman in history
to do that.

118
00:06:43,810 --> 00:06:45,310
On top of that, no photos?

119
00:06:45,310 --> 00:06:47,150
He wouldn't even let us take any photos!

120
00:06:47,210 --> 00:06:48,750
Be quiet! The Chairman will hear you.

121
00:06:48,810 --> 00:06:51,680
I don't care anymore!
I have nothing to lose.

122
00:06:52,550 --> 00:06:54,850
There's a limit to
how he can mess with people.

123
00:06:55,390 --> 00:06:56,620
Do I look like a joke to him?

124
00:06:57,990 --> 00:07:00,830
How could he humiliate me like that?

125
00:07:02,090 --> 00:07:05,200
I got my hopes up for absolutely nothing.

126
00:07:05,630 --> 00:07:08,930
And to top it all off,
I even got a nosebleed!

127
00:07:15,710 --> 00:07:18,010
- Unbelievable!
- Oh, my back!

128
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:19,140
For goodness' sake!

129
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:28,220
Mom, if you storm out of here
in a fit of anger,

130
00:07:28,220 --> 00:07:29,850
how are we supposed to make a living?

131
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:34,930
Did we starve before we moved in here?

132
00:07:35,130 --> 00:07:37,130
We got by just fine.

133
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:39,860
What happened to your plan to marry me off
to the youngest son of a tycoon family?

134
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:42,030
- Was that all a lie?
- What?

135
00:07:43,300 --> 00:07:44,500
No,

136
00:07:44,970 --> 00:07:48,310
but I'm too embarrassed
to keep living here like this.

137
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:50,040
Your back seems perfectly fine.

138
00:07:51,380 --> 00:07:55,650
Oh my, I'm dying. My poor back!

139
00:07:55,750 --> 00:07:57,380
Mom, you know what they say.

140
00:07:57,380 --> 00:07:59,150
A journey of a thousand miles
begins with one step.

141
00:07:59,620 --> 00:08:03,450
- Win over the Chairman, little by little.
- "Little by little?"

142
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:06,590
At this rate, when will he and I
legally get married...

143
00:08:06,590 --> 00:08:08,690
and get you on the family registry?

144
00:08:08,760 --> 00:08:10,530
Think about ten years ago.

145
00:08:10,530 --> 00:08:12,700
No, think about this time last year.

146
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:16,200
Remember a few months ago.

147
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:17,970
Think about where we were
and what we were doing.

148
00:08:18,140 --> 00:08:21,170
- Oh my.
- Now you can call the Chairman "honey,"

149
00:08:21,410 --> 00:08:24,180
and I've even started to call him Father.

150
00:08:24,180 --> 00:08:25,240
That's true.

151
00:08:25,940 --> 00:08:27,550
We've made great strides.

152
00:08:28,780 --> 00:08:31,480
I guess I was expecting too much too soon.

153
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:32,980
Just you watch.

154
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:35,950
I will get our marriage registered,
no matter what.

155
00:08:38,090 --> 00:08:40,990
Thank you for helping me out, Father.

156
00:08:40,990 --> 00:08:42,260
Nothing to thank me for.

157
00:08:43,090 --> 00:08:44,600
Even if you hadn't asked,

158
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:47,230
I wouldn't do anything
to jeopardize my own shares.

159
00:08:47,330 --> 00:08:48,400
You have a point.

160
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:51,170
If she had wedding photos taken with you
in a dress and all,

161
00:08:51,540 --> 00:08:54,370
that would be undeniable proof
of a common-law marriage.

162
00:08:54,810 --> 00:08:58,540
Then you'd have to give her a share
of your assets when you kick her out,

163
00:08:58,780 --> 00:09:01,850
- and that's a huge headache.
- You think I didn't think of that?

164
00:09:02,580 --> 00:09:03,580
Hang up now.

165
00:09:06,820 --> 00:09:10,350
Father, can I get you
some tea or something?

166
00:09:10,590 --> 00:09:12,490
What's your mother up to?

167
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:16,830
- She's just...
- She's made her point.

168
00:09:17,230 --> 00:09:18,360
So tell her to come down.

169
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:20,770
Or she can pack her bags and get out.

170
00:09:20,870 --> 00:09:21,930
What?

171
00:09:21,930 --> 00:09:25,240
No, she's not mad.

172
00:09:31,610 --> 00:09:32,610
What?

173
00:09:33,210 --> 00:09:35,410
You're saying you don't have a dad,
just a mom?

174
00:09:36,280 --> 00:09:38,250
No, I have a grandpa, too.

175
00:09:39,150 --> 00:09:43,020
- When did your dad pass away?
- Shit.

176
00:09:43,290 --> 00:09:44,920
You'll find that out
when you get to my house.

177
00:09:47,330 --> 00:09:48,990
Here, try doing it like this.

178
00:09:49,530 --> 00:09:51,960
There's just one difference between us.

179
00:09:52,460 --> 00:09:53,500
It's this right here.

180
00:10:04,880 --> 00:10:05,880
What?

181
00:10:10,180 --> 00:10:11,180
Here, look.

182
00:10:12,550 --> 00:10:14,890
See? Now we're exactly the same.

183
00:10:15,350 --> 00:10:16,350
You're right.

184
00:10:17,660 --> 00:10:19,920
You have a mole
behind your ear, and I don't.

185
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:24,100
- But isn't this going to wash right off?
- You worry way too much.

186
00:10:24,500 --> 00:10:26,060
It won't come off that easily.

187
00:10:26,900 --> 00:10:28,230
Besides,

188
00:10:28,230 --> 00:10:31,700
since we're only switching for one day,
you absolutely cannot get caught.

189
00:10:32,100 --> 00:10:33,100
Got it?

190
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:47,220
- I'm home.
- Hey.

191
00:10:47,220 --> 00:10:48,750
Seo Rin hasn't gone out, has she?

192
00:10:49,990 --> 00:10:51,590
She left a little while ago.

193
00:10:52,390 --> 00:10:53,960
Where in the world could she have gone?

194
00:10:54,290 --> 00:10:57,330
Is there something going on
with Seo Rin lately?

195
00:10:57,600 --> 00:11:01,200
- What do you mean?
- She seems a bit distracted these days.

196
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:03,900
It's probably
because of General Manager Kang.

197
00:11:06,800 --> 00:11:07,910
Don't worry about it.

198
00:11:08,710 --> 00:11:09,910
I'll go upstairs.

199
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:21,720
What are you writing down?
Are you an idiot?

200
00:11:24,060 --> 00:11:27,190
What if someone finds it as evidence?
Memorize it.

201
00:11:27,260 --> 00:11:30,560
Why would you throw it away?
How am I supposed to memorize all that?

202
00:11:30,630 --> 00:11:32,760
Shit. Are you stupid?

203
00:11:32,930 --> 00:11:34,730
Saying it so bluntly just feels mean.

204
00:11:35,170 --> 00:11:36,930
I'm pretty sure my IQ is higher
than yours, though.

205
00:11:37,100 --> 00:11:39,770
It's only because I don't have time
to study with my part-time jobs.

206
00:11:39,970 --> 00:11:42,410
If I actually studied,
I could've gotten into a great college.

207
00:11:43,010 --> 00:11:44,410
And a chip on your shoulder, too?

208
00:11:44,810 --> 00:11:45,810
What?

209
00:11:46,010 --> 00:11:47,080
Right.

210
00:11:50,650 --> 00:11:51,650
Do it like this.

211
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:58,060
So this is your default pose.

212
00:11:58,960 --> 00:12:00,560
But the expression is what's important.

213
00:12:01,860 --> 00:12:02,930
Like this.

214
00:12:03,230 --> 00:12:05,630
How? Like this?

215
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:11,200
Shit. What is that?
You look like a sad little puppy.

216
00:12:11,540 --> 00:12:12,740
Not like that.

217
00:12:14,040 --> 00:12:15,040
Like this.

218
00:12:16,170 --> 00:12:18,280
Looking down all cynical like that?

219
00:12:19,380 --> 00:12:22,380
But why is that your go-to expression?

220
00:12:25,380 --> 00:12:27,080
Because life is boring.

221
00:12:27,280 --> 00:12:28,290
Why?

222
00:12:28,290 --> 00:12:31,690
How can life be fun
when everything always goes my way?

223
00:12:32,020 --> 00:12:33,760
It's painfully dull and boring.

224
00:12:34,530 --> 00:12:35,730
Must be nice.

225
00:12:35,990 --> 00:12:38,900
- To have everything go your way...
- Shit.

226
00:12:39,330 --> 00:12:40,830
Are you not practicing?

227
00:12:40,830 --> 00:12:43,170
- You want to get caught?
- No.

228
00:12:44,030 --> 00:12:46,870
Look, don't I look completely
unimpressed by everything?

229
00:12:47,170 --> 00:12:48,340
Pretty similar, right?

230
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:50,810
Cynical with a bit of an attitude.

231
00:12:51,380 --> 00:12:52,380
Good.

232
00:12:53,040 --> 00:12:54,480
And if anyone asks you anything,

233
00:12:54,780 --> 00:12:58,580
just say "Okay" or "No."

234
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:02,650
It's really hard to act like you.

235
00:13:04,220 --> 00:13:05,460
Okay.

236
00:13:05,460 --> 00:13:06,620
No.

237
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:09,460
- Like this?
- This isn't going to work.

238
00:13:09,960 --> 00:13:13,730
If you do that, San Wol and Jin Hong Ju
will see through you in a second.

239
00:13:14,060 --> 00:13:17,800
They are way too sharp.
They will realize you're not me.

240
00:13:19,340 --> 00:13:22,610
Okay, so at your house, there's no dad,

241
00:13:23,010 --> 00:13:27,650
you live with your grandpa and mom,
plus your grandpa's mistress, San Wol,

242
00:13:27,710 --> 00:13:29,910
and her daughter, Jin Hong Ju, right?

243
00:13:30,180 --> 00:13:32,550
I guess you're not a total airhead
since you memorized that so fast.

244
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:37,050
And with my grandfather,
you have to lay on the charm.

245
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:39,120
Do that, and you'll be golden.

246
00:13:39,390 --> 00:13:42,030
Lay on the charm with Grandpa.

247
00:13:42,490 --> 00:13:43,490
As for my mom...

248
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:48,700
She's the one trying to kill you,
so you need to be careful, Oh Jang Mi.

249
00:13:49,470 --> 00:13:50,970
Remember that face I told you to make?

250
00:13:51,270 --> 00:13:55,410
- Keep that look and don't be intimidated.
- Don't get intimidated?

251
00:13:55,970 --> 00:13:57,310
Is she that intimidating?

252
00:13:57,440 --> 00:14:00,710
With my mom, just answer everything
with an irritated "Yes."

253
00:14:01,210 --> 00:14:04,250
And whatever San Wol and Jin Hong Ju say,

254
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:06,720
just argue with them, got it?

255
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:07,820
Okay, I'll give it a shot.

256
00:14:07,820 --> 00:14:08,890
"Yes."

257
00:14:10,490 --> 00:14:11,490
But...

258
00:14:12,220 --> 00:14:15,330
you know why I'm going into
that house, right?

259
00:14:15,330 --> 00:14:16,330
I do.

260
00:14:16,730 --> 00:14:20,300
Why we were separated as twins
and ended up living in different homes.

261
00:14:20,460 --> 00:14:21,670
That's what you want to find out, right?

262
00:14:22,330 --> 00:14:25,500
I think the person who took you
is the key to all this.

263
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:28,040
I have a feeling they hold the key
to the secret.

264
00:14:28,740 --> 00:14:31,380
- That's what I'm going to find out.
- Hey, Oh Jang Mi.

265
00:14:32,110 --> 00:14:36,080
Even if you do find something out,
don't you dare let on that you know.

266
00:14:36,380 --> 00:14:37,720
And don't get too carried away.

267
00:14:38,220 --> 00:14:41,520
You know our rule, right?
We can't get caught, no matter what.

268
00:14:41,950 --> 00:14:43,590
And let me say this one more time.

269
00:14:43,950 --> 00:14:46,220
No matter what you find out,
don't let on that you know.

270
00:14:46,490 --> 00:14:47,630
Got it?

271
00:14:47,630 --> 00:14:49,590
Or you could end up dead.

272
00:14:50,030 --> 00:14:52,130
Honestly, I'm not so sure I can do that.

273
00:14:53,330 --> 00:14:55,730
If I go into that house
and find out some secret...

274
00:14:56,630 --> 00:14:57,640
No...

275
00:14:57,640 --> 00:15:00,700
If I find out who's responsible
for what happened to our mom,

276
00:15:00,870 --> 00:15:02,540
I'd probably lose it and confront them.

277
00:15:02,540 --> 00:15:04,740
No, then this won't work.

278
00:15:05,040 --> 00:15:06,510
The deal is off.
We're not swapping places.

279
00:15:06,540 --> 00:15:07,540
Shit.

280
00:15:07,540 --> 00:15:08,880
Don't contact me again.

281
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:11,920
No, wait.

282
00:15:30,530 --> 00:15:33,800
Rin, I swear I won't let it show at all.

283
00:15:39,610 --> 00:15:40,710
You swear?

284
00:15:41,210 --> 00:15:44,320
If you act like you know everything,
there could be bloodshed.

285
00:15:44,520 --> 00:15:46,850
Listen carefully, Oh Jang Mi.
Don't you forget it.

286
00:15:47,890 --> 00:15:49,820
If you don't want to see
more blood spilled,

287
00:15:50,120 --> 00:15:52,960
- you have to keep your wits about you.
- Do you...

288
00:15:53,220 --> 00:15:56,160
already know who's responsible
for what happened to Mom?

289
00:15:57,090 --> 00:15:59,960
Of course. Didn't I tell you
I know everything?

290
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:02,970
Who is it? Tell me who it is.

291
00:16:03,330 --> 00:16:05,970
And why were we separated
in the first place?

292
00:16:05,970 --> 00:16:07,470
About all the secrets surrounding that,

293
00:16:07,870 --> 00:16:10,070
I'll tell you
when our little one-day switch is over...

294
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:14,280
with the whole truth and the proof
I have to back it up.

295
00:16:14,580 --> 00:16:17,410
What? You have proof?

296
00:16:34,830 --> 00:16:37,870
That's strange.
Since when does she keep her room so tidy?

297
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:42,170
Something's definitely off.

298
00:17:18,710 --> 00:17:20,180
I miss you, Hwa Young.

299
00:17:23,780 --> 00:17:25,550
When can we see each other?

300
00:17:42,930 --> 00:17:45,070
I want to see you, too.

301
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:48,470
But when I think about Jun Ho,

302
00:17:49,770 --> 00:17:51,210
I just can't.

303
00:18:00,280 --> 00:18:03,020
(Bomdama)

304
00:18:04,320 --> 00:18:06,360
Look, it's Tae Sook. She's working.

305
00:18:06,720 --> 00:18:07,930
Mom.

306
00:18:08,430 --> 00:18:10,090
What are you doing here? I'm working.

307
00:18:10,630 --> 00:18:12,060
Tae Pyung, why did you...

308
00:18:12,330 --> 00:18:15,430
- She kept begging me to bring her here.
- Mom.

309
00:18:18,340 --> 00:18:22,270
Still no reply from Hwa Young.
Gosh, is she that busy?

310
00:18:22,610 --> 00:18:25,640
I said the settlement worked out.
Did you hear me, honey?

311
00:18:25,680 --> 00:18:26,740
What?

312
00:18:27,740 --> 00:18:28,850
Right.

313
00:18:30,280 --> 00:18:32,220
It's a relief the settlement went through.

314
00:18:32,950 --> 00:18:36,190
But Baek Ho will freak out
if he finds out.

315
00:18:36,190 --> 00:18:37,450
Why would he freak out?

316
00:18:37,890 --> 00:18:40,590
It's not like I threatened them
into settling.

317
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:43,560
All I did was give them the money
they asked for and get the settlement.

318
00:18:43,890 --> 00:18:44,900
Mom.

319
00:18:46,760 --> 00:18:48,300
When did you get in?

320
00:18:49,630 --> 00:18:51,970
You got a settlement? From who?

321
00:18:52,040 --> 00:18:55,910
- Who do you think? Oh Jang Mi's sister.
- You mean Tae Sook?

322
00:18:56,670 --> 00:18:58,710
I don't think Jang Mi and Tae Pyung
know anything about this.

323
00:18:59,240 --> 00:19:00,910
Then that settlement is void.

324
00:19:00,910 --> 00:19:03,080
Jang Mi will be devastated
if she finds out.

325
00:19:03,380 --> 00:19:07,150
How can you stand in front of your dad
and only worry about Oh Jang Mi?

326
00:19:07,550 --> 00:19:08,750
For goodness' sake.

327
00:19:10,390 --> 00:19:11,520
I'm sorry, Dad.

328
00:19:12,360 --> 00:19:14,190
But there's something about this case
that doesn't sit right with me,

329
00:19:14,660 --> 00:19:17,430
so to have it all wrapped up
with a settlement just feels wrong.

330
00:19:17,900 --> 00:19:18,930
Baek Ho.

331
00:19:19,230 --> 00:19:22,130
Do you even care
what I think about all this?

332
00:19:24,540 --> 00:19:26,940
I've been letting this go,
but you're really crossing the line now.

333
00:19:27,300 --> 00:19:28,410
I'm sorry.

334
00:19:29,040 --> 00:19:30,370
I'm going to go outside.

335
00:19:31,070 --> 00:19:32,080
Kang Baek Ho.

336
00:19:33,040 --> 00:19:34,310
You and I need to talk.

337
00:19:39,050 --> 00:19:42,350
Baek Ho.
Let's have a frank discussion about this.

338
00:19:42,950 --> 00:19:45,320
You keep saying
that this case feels wrong...

339
00:19:45,320 --> 00:19:49,190
and accusing me
of causing your girlfriend's dad to die.

340
00:19:49,260 --> 00:19:51,130
- That's not what I'm saying.
- Let me finish.

341
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:56,330
Every time you've said things like that,
it's been upsetting, but I held my tongue.

342
00:19:56,530 --> 00:19:59,570
Because, at the end of the day,
he died in the car I was driving.

343
00:20:00,040 --> 00:20:02,040
I felt like a guilty man
has no right to complain.

344
00:20:02,310 --> 00:20:04,210
I understand how you feel, Dad.

345
00:20:04,210 --> 00:20:05,810
But like I've said over and over,

346
00:20:06,210 --> 00:20:08,610
there were too many strange things
surrounding his death.

347
00:20:08,810 --> 00:20:13,050
Look, that's just circumstantial.
Nothing's actually been proven, right?

348
00:20:13,850 --> 00:20:17,350
And the fact is that he died
in the car that I was driving,

349
00:20:18,320 --> 00:20:20,090
so what more is there to question?

350
00:20:21,220 --> 00:20:23,830
- Dad...
- I've held my tongue, though I'm upset.

351
00:20:24,430 --> 00:20:26,600
If you ever say that kind of garbage
in front of me again,

352
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:28,730
I won't put up with it anymore.

353
00:20:29,530 --> 00:20:31,740
Enough is enough.

354
00:20:31,940 --> 00:20:34,910
Why do you always take her side over me...

355
00:20:34,970 --> 00:20:37,410
and constantly remind me
of what I did wrong?

356
00:20:38,280 --> 00:20:39,780
It's like you're trying to torture me.

357
00:20:42,410 --> 00:20:43,450
I'm sorry.

358
00:20:44,550 --> 00:20:46,150
If that's how it made you feel,

359
00:20:46,720 --> 00:20:47,750
then I'm truly sorry.

360
00:20:49,250 --> 00:20:52,560
I didn't fully understand
how you were feeling.

361
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:54,990
I'll be more considerate in the future.

362
00:20:56,090 --> 00:20:57,560
Good grief.

363
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:07,570
Looks like Baek Ho is finally
starting to understand his father now.

364
00:21:08,310 --> 00:21:12,180
How could he just cast his father aside
and only take his girlfriend's side?

365
00:21:13,010 --> 00:21:17,210
It's true what they say,
"A son is a son until he gets a wife."

366
00:21:26,820 --> 00:21:28,730
- Right now?
- Yes.

367
00:21:29,030 --> 00:21:30,830
You mean you want to do
the one-day switch right now?

368
00:21:31,160 --> 00:21:33,160
Yes, why waste time?

369
00:21:37,100 --> 00:21:41,000
What? Do you need to prepare?
We're just switching for a night.

370
00:21:41,410 --> 00:21:45,410
- But I still need to mentally prepare...
- Shit.

371
00:21:46,040 --> 00:21:48,410
If you keep stalling,
I might change my mind.

372
00:21:48,810 --> 00:21:51,450
I'm super fickle. You know what I'm like.

373
00:21:51,820 --> 00:21:55,020
- Should I just call it off?
- No, wait! Don't do that.

374
00:21:55,920 --> 00:21:56,920
Okay, fine.

375
00:21:57,350 --> 00:22:00,120
- Then let's switch right now.
- That's more like it.

376
00:22:00,620 --> 00:22:02,130
I'm having second thoughts myself.

377
00:22:21,550 --> 00:22:22,550
Oh my!

378
00:22:33,160 --> 00:22:34,160
It looks good on you.

379
00:22:37,260 --> 00:22:38,900
I hope I can get used to this fast.

380
00:22:46,970 --> 00:22:49,470
Seo Rin, you're just like me.

381
00:22:50,670 --> 00:22:51,810
Not yet.

382
00:22:59,080 --> 00:23:00,120
I feel dizzy.

383
00:23:02,320 --> 00:23:03,950
Take all of these.

384
00:23:04,290 --> 00:23:06,890
- Say you went to the department store.
- What?

385
00:23:09,990 --> 00:23:12,830
You buy this many clothes all at once?

386
00:23:12,960 --> 00:23:14,100
Shit.

387
00:23:14,100 --> 00:23:15,500
You have too many questions.

388
00:23:42,390 --> 00:23:43,390
Oh my...

389
00:23:47,360 --> 00:23:48,370
This is the place.

390
00:23:52,070 --> 00:23:55,070
- This place is incredible.
- Don't be intimidated.

391
00:23:55,710 --> 00:23:57,640
People are the same everywhere.

392
00:24:01,280 --> 00:24:02,980
Here, go nuts with this.

393
00:24:03,950 --> 00:24:06,750
- With this?
- It's my money, so feel free to go wild.

394
00:24:07,220 --> 00:24:09,520
You can't have a rich-girl experience
without money to burn.

395
00:24:10,090 --> 00:24:12,820
Right, we need to swap phones too.

396
00:24:13,460 --> 00:24:14,460
Right.

397
00:24:18,760 --> 00:24:23,130
But we're only switching lives
for one day.

398
00:24:23,200 --> 00:24:24,230
Just for one day.

399
00:24:25,400 --> 00:24:27,940
You'll be me, and I'll be you.

400
00:24:28,170 --> 00:24:31,140
I get to see how a normal person lives,
and you get to live like a rich heiress.

401
00:24:31,840 --> 00:24:36,050
This is fun.
This is the most exciting thing ever.

402
00:24:36,210 --> 00:24:38,180
This is so much fun and so thrilling.

403
00:24:40,820 --> 00:24:44,150
Grandfather, Mom, San Wol, and Hong Ju.

404
00:24:44,520 --> 00:24:46,820
Cynical and defiant.

405
00:24:51,290 --> 00:24:52,460
Taxi!

406
00:24:52,700 --> 00:24:53,760
Hurry, go inside.

407
00:24:54,100 --> 00:24:55,130
I am Oh Jang Mi now.

408
00:24:55,870 --> 00:24:56,870
Seo Rin!

409
00:24:58,070 --> 00:24:59,070
Wait!

410
00:25:01,100 --> 00:25:02,110
My mom...

411
00:25:03,010 --> 00:25:07,180
- She regressed after the accident.
- I know.

412
00:25:07,580 --> 00:25:08,580
I've seen her before.

413
00:25:09,710 --> 00:25:11,310
Is there anything you don't know?

414
00:25:11,310 --> 00:25:14,020
Like I said, I know everything.

415
00:25:14,550 --> 00:25:15,720
I almost forgot.

416
00:25:17,020 --> 00:25:18,020
Here.

417
00:25:19,760 --> 00:25:21,120
Don't get caught.

418
00:25:23,460 --> 00:25:26,030
My room is on the second floor,
all the way to the right.

419
00:25:26,730 --> 00:25:29,600
And make sure you don't get caught
being Oh Jang Mi either.

420
00:25:30,000 --> 00:25:31,800
Okay. It's a deal!

421
00:25:45,720 --> 00:25:46,720
My mom...

422
00:25:47,750 --> 00:25:49,250
can finally hold the daughter
she thought was lost,

423
00:25:50,320 --> 00:25:52,190
even if it's just for one day.

424
00:25:59,960 --> 00:26:00,960
Yes!

425
00:26:26,560 --> 00:26:29,090
Have you calmed down now?

426
00:26:30,430 --> 00:26:32,660
Who said I was angry?

427
00:26:33,300 --> 00:26:34,560
I was not angry.

428
00:26:35,630 --> 00:26:37,230
I was just disappointed.

429
00:26:38,440 --> 00:26:41,240
And I was embarrassed by
what other people would think.

430
00:26:41,300 --> 00:26:43,440
Why do you care so much
what other people think?

431
00:26:43,610 --> 00:26:46,640
To me, it's very important.

432
00:26:46,640 --> 00:26:48,410
Why else do people get married?

433
00:26:48,850 --> 00:26:51,750
- It's all about keeping up appearances.
- What?

434
00:26:51,750 --> 00:26:53,020
Am I wrong?

435
00:26:53,020 --> 00:26:55,350
Imagine a man and a woman living together
without a wedding ceremony.

436
00:26:55,690 --> 00:26:58,520
Without exchanging vows
that they'll build a life together...

437
00:26:58,520 --> 00:26:59,920
before everyone,

438
00:26:59,990 --> 00:27:02,430
they'd just live together
when they feel like it,

439
00:27:02,660 --> 00:27:05,000
and break up the second
they get tired of each other.

440
00:27:05,630 --> 00:27:10,170
But marriage is also a promise
you make in front of everyone.

441
00:27:10,630 --> 00:27:12,600
A promise that you'll make it work.

442
00:27:13,140 --> 00:27:14,740
Everyone, have a glass of wine.

443
00:27:15,010 --> 00:27:16,570
Come on, can't you read the room?

444
00:27:16,840 --> 00:27:20,510
Did you have to ruin the mood
during such a serious conversation?

445
00:27:20,580 --> 00:27:22,110
Good idea, Hong Ju. Let's have a drink.

446
00:27:23,610 --> 00:27:25,020
For crying out loud.

447
00:27:32,490 --> 00:27:35,090
What's the update? Did you find Seo Rin?

448
00:27:35,260 --> 00:27:37,760
- They say she's right outside the house.
- Outside the house?

449
00:27:38,700 --> 00:27:40,230
What's she doing out there?

450
00:27:40,360 --> 00:27:42,900
My guys say she's been sitting out front
for the last 30 minutes.

451
00:27:43,570 --> 00:27:46,970
See? I told you something's off with her.

452
00:27:47,500 --> 00:27:50,710
Why does she always have to make me worry?

453
00:27:51,410 --> 00:27:53,410
She made me come all the way back
to the office.

454
00:27:53,780 --> 00:27:55,610
She is going to be the death of me.

455
00:27:56,250 --> 00:27:57,280
Wait a second.

456
00:28:05,890 --> 00:28:09,060
Oh Jang Mi, you're so pathetic.

457
00:28:09,930 --> 00:28:12,930
Why can't I just go in?
What am I doing out here?

458
00:28:13,260 --> 00:28:14,730
I've been at this too long already.

459
00:28:18,170 --> 00:28:19,170
Whatever.

460
00:28:21,500 --> 00:28:22,840
If I get caught, so be it.

461
00:28:49,270 --> 00:28:50,800
(The First Man)

462
00:28:51,030 --> 00:28:53,500
You're not Jang Mi! You're Tok Hee!

463
00:28:53,840 --> 00:28:56,510
What? Does she know I'm not Oh Jang Mi?

464
00:28:56,870 --> 00:28:59,110
CEO Chae Hwa Young is Seo Rin's mother?

465
00:28:59,510 --> 00:29:03,750
So that's why she did everything she could
to keep Seo Rin and me from meeting.

466
00:29:04,410 --> 00:29:05,880
After everything she's done,
you still don't get it?

467
00:29:06,150 --> 00:29:07,920
I have proof.

468
00:29:07,920 --> 00:29:10,090
Chae Hwa Young, that horrible woman.

469
00:29:10,450 --> 00:29:11,520
I won't let her get away with this.

470
00:29:12,860 --> 00:29:14,860
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
